commit d2feb56073bf3b00659f4387a4a9fa53510cffb2
Author: Nick Reynolds <ndreynolds@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Sep 8 01:28:30 2011 -0400

    Issue dir restructure; BaseFile, JSONFile, ConfigFile classes.
    
    Another night of hacking with too few commits:
    
    core:
        * Comments are now stored as separate files.
        * The issue SHA is the dir name.
        * The issue is stored as a file, issue
        * Still JSON-based.
        * Delete Item class in favor of *File classes. The BaseFile
          handles attribute getting and setting, subclasses handle
          saving to disk using different formats.
        * Working Config class, even includes a gitconfig parser.
    
    web:
        * Adds showdown.js to web issue commenting (markdown preview)
        * Various margin/color/padding/border tweaks.
        * Flash message: 'Running Hopper locally as [name]'.
    
    hpr:
        * Created the dir, will hold CLI tools.
    
    The tests probably don't pass.

